  "body": "Currently our code responsible for getting the first pod for logs or attach allows specifying a timeout, how long to wait for that: see [here](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/1cb737fb970a65be2b3ff21cbf00196359b56cd3/pkg/kubectl/cmd/util/factory_object_mapping.go#L229) and [here](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/1cb737fb970a65be2b3ff21cbf00196359b56cd3/pkg/kubectl/cmd/util/factory_object_mapping.go#L360) but the value in there is hard-coded. It would be nice to expose this option to user through `kubectl` flag.",
